Liverpool supporters will stage a protest on Tuesday night against the mounting costs of tickets in the Barclays Premier League .
The die-hard contingent of fans are staying away from The KC Stadium after Hull City charged Liverpool fans £ 50 for their sets .
Last season , the same seats were sold for £ 35 .
Liverpool fans were charged £ 16 for tickets when they went to Hull in the FA Cup semi-final at Hull game .
Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers says he of supporters ' right to protest .